Pottinger County was named in honour of the first Governor of Hong Kong Sir Henry Pottinger , first Baronet (1789-1856).
Pottinger County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located to the south west of the Namoi River and Mooki River , near Gunnedah .
